message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper discusses the use of neural networks for natural language processing tasks, specifically question-answering using BERT. This falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of DeepLIFT, a technique for interpreting neural network predictions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper analyzes patterns in the model's attention values, which could also fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
